'''Cite''' makes it possible to add footnotes to a page.

<!--T:87-->
See <tvar name=1>{{ll|Extension:Cite}}</tvar> for technical details.

== Usage == <!--T:96-->

<!--T:97-->
The basic concept of the <tvar name=1>{{tag|ref|open}}</tvar> tag is that it inserts the text enclosed by the ref tags as a footnote in a designated section, which you indicate with the placeholder tag <tvar name=2>{{tag|references|single}}</tvar>.

<!--T:98-->
Additional placeholder tags <tvar name=1>{{tag|references|single}}</tvar> can be inserted in the text, and all <tvar name=2>{{tag|ref|open}}</tvar> tags up to that point, in that group, will be inserted there.

<!--T:99-->
If you forget to include <tvar name=1>{{tag|references|single}}</tvar> in the article, the footnotes will not disappear, but the references will be displayed at the end of the page.
</translate>

