<translate><!--T:238--> In that case, the <tvar name=1><code>responsive</code></tvar> attribute is used to configure that behavior.</translate>
<translate><!--T:239--> On wikis with the default configuration, this will happen on every page; on others, you need to activate it.</translate> <translate><!--T:325--> On wikis with the default configuration, the responsive behavior can be disabled with <tvar name=1><syntaxhighlight lang=html inline><references responsive="0" /></syntaxhighlight></tvar>.</translate>

<translate><!--T:124--> If a page includes more than one <tvar name=1>{{tag|references|single}}</tvar> list, each list includes the <tvar name=2>{{tag|ref|open}}</tvar> tags defined after the previous references list.</translate>
<translate><!--T:202--> If these references lists are produced by templates, each one lists the ref tags defined before the first references list, and there is an error message saying that there is a ref tag but not a references list.</translate>

