=== Citing different parts of the same source === <!--T:137-->
</translate>
<translate><!--T:138--> When several parts from the same work are used as references in an article, you can cluster them in the reference section.</translate>
<translate><!--T:251--> This gives readers a way to identify which references originate from the same source.</translate>
<translate><!--T:252--> It also allows you to cite different parts of the same source without repeating the entire source every time.</translate>

