<translate>
===Separating references from text=== <!--T:148-->
</translate>
<translate><!--T:149--> In-text references make it easy to copy the text to another page; on the other hand, they make it hard to read.</translate>
<translate><!--T:260--> References containing a lot of data, quotes or elaborate citation templates can make up a significantly larger fraction of the source than the text that will actually be visible.</translate>
<translate><!--T:261--> To avoid this, you can move some or all of the references into the <tvar name=1>{{tag|references|single}}</tvar> section, to the place where they will actually appear to the reader.</translate>

