=== Adding an automatic heading before the references list === <!--T:161-->
</translate>
<translate><!--T:162--> Up to MediaWiki 1.28, one could use the system message <tvar name=1><code>MediaWiki:Cite references prefix</code></tvar> to define a wiki-wide heading which would be automatically inserted before each references list.</translate> <translate><!--T:273--> In MediaWiki 1.29, [[<tvar name=1>gerrit:c/mediawiki/extensions/Cite/+/229852</tvar>|this system message was removed]].</translate> <translate><!--T:274--> A hacky way to enter a headline now is to add the following code to <tvar name=1><code>MediaWiki:Common.js</code></tvar>:</translate>

<syntaxhighlight lang="javascript" copy>
$(document).ready(function(){
    $('.mw-references-wrap').before('<h2><translate nowrap><!--T:275--> References</translate></h2>');
});
</syntaxhighlight>

<translate>
<!--T:310-->
Note that this adds the header unconditionally, i.e. if you already have the header it gets added again thus creating duplicated headers.

